CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1946, pg. 1, reads: "An Array Of Stars - Pittsburgh's famous sons and daughters, who came home Thursday night to do a show for the Frogs at Syria Mosque, talk about old time in Smoky City...Harris Photo."Supplemental courier article: "Maxine Sullivan, Billy Ecksteine, and Mary Lou Williams have accepted the Frogs' invitation to be among the headlines for its Nite O'Stars, Aug. 7. They, among other attending Pittsburghers who have made good in the big time, will be honored by this paper, which will award all of them.""BILLY... Rowe's NOTE BOOK." 1946.The Pittsburgh Courier (1911-1950), Jul 13, 22. http://search.proquest.com/docview/202168304?accountid=9901.
TitMainTitle: Mary Lou Williams seated at piano with P. Lawrence Peeler standing behind her, in Syria Mosque for Night of Stars
